## Code Blocks

Always specify language:

```cpp
#include <iostream>

int main() {
    // English comments
    std::cout << "Output" << std::endl;
    return 0;
}
```

## LaTeX Math

Inline: `$O(n \log n)$`

Block:
```
$$
T(n) = 2T(n/2) + O(n)
$$
```

## Language Rules

- **Content**: Bulgarian (Cyrillic)
- **Code**: English (comments, variable names)
- **Technical terms**: English when standard (e.g., "Big-O", "hash table")
- **Component props**: English

## Tags

**Standard tags**:
- General: `data-structures`, `algorithms`, `cpp`, `exercises`, `practice`
- Topics: `arrays`, `linked-lists`, `trees`, `graphs`, `hash-tables`
- Concepts: `complexity`, `recursion`, `sorting`, `searching`
- Difficulty: `easy`, `medium`, `hard` (in ExerciseCard only)

