## Testing Workflow

```bash
# 1. Start dev server
cd docusaurus-site
npm start

# 2. Check http://localhost:3000

# 3. Build (checks for errors)
npm run build

# 4. If successful, commit
git add docs/XX-topic-name/
git commit -m "Add lecture XX: Topic"
git push origin main
```

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

1. ‚ùå Missing imports at top of file
2. ‚ùå Wrong component paths (use `@site/src/components/...`)
3. ‚ùå Mixing Bulgarian/English inconsistently
4. ‚ùå Forgetting "–î–æ–ø—ä–ª–Ω–∏—Ç–µ–ª–Ω–∏ –†–µ—Å—É—Ä—Å–∏" section
5. ‚ùå Not using components (plain markdown is less engaging)
6. ‚ùå Missing frontmatter or wrong format
7. ‚ùå Incorrect directory naming
8. ‚ùå Not testing locally before push

